      <scopecontent>
         <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
         <p>This collection consists of the papers of the
         Charlottesville-Albemarle Association for the Fine Arts, an
         affiliate of the Virginia Museum of Fine Arts, 1982-1997, ca.
         500 items (2 Hollinger boxes). The records include corporate
         records, financial and bank statements, legal papers
         concerning the tax-exempt status of the organization,
         insurance papers, annual reports of the Virginia State
         Corporation Commission, membership and mailing lists,
         correspondence with the Virginia Museum of Fine Arts, by-laws,
         minutes of meetings, papers about films, workshops, publicity,
         safaris, and the dissolution of the chapter.</p>
      </scopecontent>
